Thailand Stocks: Bangchak Petroleum, Italian-Thai, True Corp

-- B y   A n u c h i t   N g u y e n
-- 
2011-08-31T06:01:46Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-31/thailand-stocks-bangchak-petroleum-ptt-exploration-true-corp.html
Shares of the following companies
had unusual moves in  Thailand  trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of the 12:30 p.m. break in
Bangkok.  The SET Index rose 12.70 points, or 1.2 percent, to
1,057.67, heading for the highest close since Aug. 22. The gauge
has lost 6.7 percent in August, set for the largest drop since
October 2008.  Bangchak Petroleum Pcl (BCP)  , a state-controlled
refiner, increased 2.4 percent to 21.70 baht, set for the
highest close since Aug. 23. The company will pay an interim
dividend of 0.65 baht a share, it said in a regulatory filing.  Italian-Thai Development Pcl (ITD)  , Thailand’s largest
construction company, gained 1.8 percent to 4.48 baht. The
company said a venture won a contract worth 213.39 million baht
to install an undersea cable network for state-owned CAT Telecom
Pcl, it said in a regulatory filing.  True Corp. (TRUE TB), the operator of Thailand’s third-
largest mobile phone network, rose 1.6 percent to 3.92 baht,
poised for the largest increase since Aug. 17. The company plans
to invest 25 billion baht ($833 million) to build a high-speed
mobile phone network, Chief Financial Officer Noppadol Dej-Udom
said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Anuchit Nguyen in Bangkok at 
 anguyen@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
